			<![CDATA[<textformat leading="12"><font size="14"></font><br><br><font size="13">International Coastal Cleanup, for example, was a statewide beach cleanup in Texas in 1986.<br>To handle mountains of plastic trash until ships reach port, the U.S.<br>Navy has recently developed onboard processors to compact and sanitize plastic trash.<br>This equipment has been on all Navy ships since 1999, and has military and commercial applications worldwide.<br>When compressed into blocks, thirty days' worth can be stored in the space that would be filled by one day's worth of uncompacted plastic trash.<br>A 300-person Navy destroyer generates about 35 cubic feet of plastic waste <br>per day, which is compressed into 5 to 6 disks.</font></textformat>]]>
